## 2. Clockify

### Overview
- **Market Position:** Budget-friendly Toggl alternative
- **Users:** 2M+
- **Pricing:** Free (unlimited users!) → Basic ($5/user/mo) → Pro ($8/user/mo)

### Strengths
- ✅ **Free tier is generous:** Unlimited users, projects, time entries
- ✅ Advanced reporting (custom filters, exports)
- ✅ Billable rates, invoicing
- ✅ Kiosk mode (office clock-in/out)
- ✅ GPS tracking (mobile)

### Weaknesses
- ❌ **Ugly, outdated UI:** "Old-fashioned" interface (per reviews)
- ❌ **Intrusive monitoring:** Screenshots every 5min (optional, but creepy)
- ❌ **Manual only:** No automatic time tracking
- ❌ **Slow mobile app:** Bugs reported
- ❌ **Cloud-first:** Privacy concerns same as Toggl

### Comparison to Toggl
- **UI:** Toggl wins (modern, beautiful)
- **Reporting:** Clockify wins (more flexible)
- **Pricing:** Clockify wins (free tier)
- **Privacy:** Both fail (cloud-first)

**Neuman Brain Advantage:** We can match Clockify's free tier + Toggl's UI + add privacy.

