## 4. Rize.io

### Overview
- **Market Position:** AI-powered focus tracker (premium)
- **Users:** 10K+ (knowledge workers, developers)
- **Pricing:** ~$15/mo (macOS, Windows apps)

### Strengths
- ✅ **AI productivity coach:** Real-time suggestions ("take a break", "you're distracted")
- ✅ **Focus quality metrics:** Deep work score, context switching detection
- ✅ **Automatic categorization:** AI categorizes apps/websites
- ✅ **Break management:** Smart break notifications
- ✅ **Focus music:** Integrated ambient sounds
- ✅ **Distraction blocking:** App/website blocking during focus sessions

### Weaknesses
- ❌ **Expensive:** $15/mo (no free tier)
- ❌ **Cloud-sync required:** Data goes to Rize servers
- ❌ **No manual tracking:** Automatic only
- ❌ **No reporting/invoicing:** Focus metrics only, not for billing

### Unique Features (Neuman Brain Should Copy)
1. **Focus Score:** % of time in deep work (>2hr uninterrupted sessions)
2. **Context Switching:** Count of project/app switches per day
3. **Best Productivity Time:** Heatmap showing when you're most focused
4. **AI Coach:** Weekly insights ("You had 12 hours of deep work, +20% from last week")

**Neuman Brain Advantage:** We can build these features with **local AI** (user's API key = privacy preserved).

