## 6. RescueTime

### Overview
- **Market Position:** Original automatic time tracker (since 2008)
- **Users:** 2M+
- **Pricing:** Free → Premium ($12/mo)

### Strengths
- ✅ **Automatic tracking:** Completely hands-off
- ✅ **Automatic categorization:** Business, Communication, Design, etc.
- ✅ **Productivity score:** Rates time as productive, neutral, or distracting
- ✅ **Goals & alerts:** Set weekly goals, get notifications
- ✅ **Focus sessions:** Block distracting sites
- ✅ **Long history:** 15+ years of data (for power users)

### Weaknesses
- ❌ **Privacy nightmare:** Tracks everything (window titles, URLs, activity)
- ❌ **Cloud-first:** All data uploaded to RescueTime servers
- ❌ **No manual tracking:** Can't add time entries
- ❌ **No invoicing:** Focus on productivity, not billing
- ❌ **Slow mobile app:** Poor reviews

### Why Users Choose It
- "Set it and forget it" appeal (zero friction)
- Good for personal productivity awareness
- Visual reports are motivating

**Neuman Brain Approach:** Offer **opt-in** automatic tracking (ActivityWatch-style extension) with **user-controlled** privacy settings.

