## Key Insights

### 1. Privacy is a Major Gap
- **Finding:** Only ActivityWatch is truly local-first
- **Opportunity:** Neuman Brain can own the "privacy-first time tracking" market
- **Target Users:** Developers, privacy advocates, GDPR-conscious companies

### 2. Focus Metrics are Premium
- **Finding:** Only Rize ($15/mo) and RescueTime (basic) offer productivity insights
- **Opportunity:** We can offer focus metrics **for free** (Rize charges premium)
- **Differentiator:** Deep work score, context switching, best productivity time

### 3. Manual + Automatic Hybrid is Rare
- **Finding:** Most tools are either manual (Toggl) OR automatic (RescueTime)
- **Opportunity:** Offer **both** with user control (manual by default, opt-in automatic)
- **UX:** User chooses tracking level (privacy slider: manual → browser extension → desktop app)

### 4. Developer Tools are Fragmented
- **Finding:** WakaTime (IDE only), Toggl (no Git integration), Taskwarrior (CLI only)
- **Opportunity:** Be the **best developer time tracker** (keyboard shortcuts, Git integration, CLI future)

### 5. Expensive for What You Get
- **Finding:** Toggl Premium ($18/mo) for invoicing, Rize ($15/mo) for focus metrics
- **Opportunity:** Offer advanced features **free** (local-first = no server costs)

