## Competitive Threats

### Short-Term (0-12 months)
- **Toggl adds privacy features:** Unlikely (cloud infrastructure baked in)
- **Clockify improves UI:** Possible, but slow-moving company
- **ActivityWatch adds invoicing:** Unlikely (focused on automatic tracking)

### Long-Term (12-24 months)
- **Rize.io drops price:** Possible if growth stalls
- **New competitor emerges:** Privacy-first time tracker (we'd be first-mover)
- **Big tech enters market:** Google/Microsoft adds time tracking to Workspace/365

### Mitigation Strategy
- **Be first to market:** Privacy-first + beautiful UX + free
- **Build moat:** Native integrations (Kanban, Calendar, Notes) that external tools can't match
- **Open-source:** Community contributions accelerate development
- **Network effects:** Users customize widgets, share templates (future marketplace)

